The Ebonyi State Governor, David Umahi, on Monday announced the approval of N5,000 travel allowance to each of the 2,200 Batch B Stream 1 Corps members who ended their orientation course on Monday.

He also approved N2 million for corps members who took part in the parade.

The governor also gave N400 million to the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) in Ebonyi State for the renovation of the scheme’s orientation camp in Afikpko North Local Government Area.

All the monies are expected to come from the state government’s coffers.

Mr Umahi also approved various cash sums to the staff of NYSC and military officers who trained the corps members.